%N A396161 First column of the triangular array with T(0, m) = m^m and T(n, m) = T(n - 1, m + 3) - T(n - 1, m + 2).
%C A396161 This sequence is obtained by iterating the shift-difference operator E^2*(E - 1) on f(m) = m^m and evaluating at m = 0, where E is the shift operator.
%F A396161 a(n) = Sum_{k=0..n} (-1)^(n - k)*binomial(n, k)*(2*n + k)^(2*n + k), with 0^0 = 1.
%e A396161 The triangular array begins:
%e A396161   m:   0     1         2          3          4       5      ...
%e A396161   -------------------------------------------------------------
%e A396161   n =  0     1         1          4          27      256    ...
%e A396161   n =  1     23        40662      339512814    ...
%e A396161   n =  2     40662     339512814      ...
%e A396161   n =  3     339512814     ...
%e A396161 a(1) = 3^3 - 2^2 = 23.
